06/05/2005
ANKARA, Turkey -- Officials say police arrested a suicide bomber shortly before she tried to enter a police station in Diyarbakir.
In a statement Thursday (5 May), police identified the woman as a member of the banned Kurdistan Workers Party.
She was found carrying C-4 explosives.
The incident happened late Wednesday.
On Sunday, police detained two people carrying explosives on board a passenger bus travelling to Istanbul from Diyarbakir.
(Reuters - 05/05/05)
